<p>Pronouns: he/him/his</p>

<h3 id="description">Description</h3>

<p>This prototyping-oriented class introduces students to the creative affordances of physical computing, or the practice of interfacing digital system with the outside world, by way of hands-on experiments across a continuum of technologies. Students will learn programming concepts (Python3), and basic electronics, as well as strategies for their interaction, via the <a href="https://www.adafruit.com/product/3405">HUZZAH32</a>. Regular critiques will provide an opportunity for students to share their research and prototypes with their colleagues as well as receive direct feedback from the instructor.</p>

